&lt;p&gt;Backblaze is the object storage leader in the open cloud movement, fueling customer success with cloud storage built purposefully to unlock budgets, unburden administrators, and unleash innovators. Together with our partners, we’re helping customers break free from the restrictive, overpriced legacy solutions that hold them back, and blaze forward with the full power of the open cloud in their hands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2007, we scaled the business with less than $3 million in outside funding until 2021, when we did a traditional IPO on the Nasdaq stock exchange. Today, Backblaze generates over $100m in revenue and is the leading specialized storage cloud - managing over three billion gigabytes of data storage for 500K+ customers in 175+ countries, including businesses, developers, IT professionals, and individuals. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;But while there is a lot to celebrate in our past, there is almost as much opportunity ahead of us. We are seeking an &lt;strong&gt;AI Enablement Director&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Backblaze is executing an ambitious, company-wide AI transformation program that is fundamentally reshaping how our organization operates at scale. This is not a theoretical research project - it is a live, high-impact initiative with production deployments already in production. We are driven by a commitment to operational excellence and tangible results, and this role sits at the very center of that mission. You will be responsible for shaping the path forward, ensuring that our AI initiatives deliver clear, measurable value that drives the business forward. This role sits at the center of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/posts/glebbudman_controversial-take-the-exec-i-put-in-activity-7373409399907807232-2ZU4/&quot;&gt;Reporting to the CHRO&lt;/a&gt;, you will lead the AI use case lifecycle, managing everything from initial intake to final production. Your responsibilities include scoping complex workflows, architecting innovative solutions, overseeing pilot programs, and precisely measuring the impact of these changes. Partnering closely with functional directors, you will identify high-potential areas for AI integration and process transformation, ensuring these initiatives translate into tangible operational results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The program has a simple test: by Q3, we should be able to answer &quot;what has AI actually delivered this year?&quot; in a single slide with numbers. You are the person who makes that slide possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the use case pipeline.&lt;/strong&gt; Triage incoming requests, refine problem statements, size value, and maintain a prioritized queue across functions. Lead each use case through discovery, scoping, pilot, and launch - coordinating functional owners, IT, Engineering, Legal, and Finance as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do the workflow work.&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct structured current-state assessments with department teams. Map how work actually happens today. Find where volume, repetition, or research intensity make AI a strong fit - and surface the use cases that would never appear in a top-down scan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design the right solution.&lt;/strong&gt; Evaluate whether a given workflow calls for an off-the-shelf tool, a prompt layer, a vendor product, or a custom build. Engage Engineering and IT when integration or custom development is required. Document baselines before launch. Measure the delta after.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Govern the tool stack.&lt;/strong&gt; Own the AI vendor evaluation process end-to-end: fit assessment, security and privacy review, pilots, and build-vs-buy recommendations. Maintain the AI Tool Registry with zero ungoverned deployments. Track spend per team monthly with cost-p

